#: src/guides/adding_languages.md:1
msgid "Adding new languages to Helix"
msgstr ""

#: src/guides/adding_languages.md:3
msgid ""
"In order to add a new language to Helix, you will need to follow the steps "
"below."
msgstr ""

#: src/guides/adding_languages.md:6
msgid "Language configuration"
msgstr ""

#: src/guides/adding_languages.md:8
msgid ""
"Add a new `[[language]]` entry in the `languages.toml` file and provide the "
"necessary configuration for the new language. For more information on "
"language configuration, refer to the [language configuration section](../"
"languages.md) of the documentation. A new language server can be added by "
"extending the `[language-server]` table in the same file."
msgstr ""

#: src/guides/adding_languages.md:13
msgid ""
"If you are adding a new language or updating an existing language server "
"configuration, run the command `cargo xtask docgen` to update the [Language "
"Support](../lang-support.md) documentation."
msgstr ""

#: src/guides/adding_languages.md:17
msgid ""
"ðŸ’¡ If you are adding a new Language Server configuration, make sure to "
"update the [Language Server Wiki](https://github.com/helix-editor/helix/wiki/"
"Language-Server-Configurations) with the installation instructions."
msgstr ""

#: src/guides/adding_languages.md:22
msgid "Grammar configuration"
msgstr "æ–‡æ³•çµ„æ…‹"

#: src/guides/adding_languages.md:24
msgid ""
"If a tree-sitter grammar is available for the new language, add a new "
"`[[grammar]]` entry to the `languages.toml` file."
msgstr ""

#: src/guides/adding_languages.md:26
msgid ""
"If you are testing the grammar locally, you can use the `source.path` key "
"with an absolute path to the grammar. However, before submitting a pull "
"request, make sure to switch to using `source.git`."
msgstr ""

#: src/guides/adding_languages.md:30
msgid "Queries"
msgstr "æŸ¥è©¢"

#: src/guides/adding_languages.md:32
msgid ""
"In order to provide syntax highlighting and indentation for the new "
"language, you will need to add queries."
msgstr ""

#: src/guides/adding_languages.md:34
msgid ""
"Create a new directory for the language with the path `runtime/queries/"
"<name>/`."
msgstr ""

#: src/guides/adding_languages.md:36
msgid ""
"Refer to the [tree-sitter website](https://tree-sitter.github.io/tree-"
"sitter/3-syntax-highlighting.html#highlights) for more information on "
"writing queries."
msgstr ""

#: src/guides/adding_languages.md:39
msgid ""
"A list of highlight captures can be found [on the themes page](https://docs."
"helix-editor.com/themes.html#scopes)."
msgstr ""

#: src/guides/adding_languages.md:41
msgid "Common issues"
msgstr "å¸¸è¦‹è­°é¡Œ"

#: src/guides/adding_languages.md:43
msgid ""
"If you encounter errors when running Helix after switching branches, you may "
"need to update the tree-sitter grammars. Run the command `hx --grammar "
"fetch` to fetch the grammars and `hx --grammar build` to build any out-of-"
"date grammars."
msgstr ""

#: src/guides/adding_languages.md:47
msgid ""
"If a parser is causing a segfault, or you want to remove it, make sure to "
"remove the compiled parser located at `runtime/grammars/<name>.so`."
msgstr ""

#: src/guides/adding_languages.md:49
msgid ""
"If you are attempting to add queries and Helix is unable to locate them, "
"ensure that the environment variable `HELIX_RUNTIME` is set to the location "
"of the `runtime` folder you're developing in."
msgstr ""
